The brighter the colour, the higher the accessibility at the peaks (meaning high accessibility yellow, low accessibility blue)
The values for depth indicate the number of reads that mapped to each peak, with a darker colour for higher read numbers and vice versa. 

It can be inferred from the heat map that the stressed animals show higher NR3C1 motif accessibility than the control animals. (as these are glucocorticoid receptors, a higher accessibility in stressed animals would make sense.)
